name: cervical large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma
definition: A cervix carcinoma that has_material_basis_in neuroendocrine tissue and is characerized by a diffuse, organoid, trabecular, or cord-like pattern of neoplastic cells with abundant cytoplasm, large nuclei, prominent nucleoli, and a high mitotic rate.
